desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William De Marbury was born in 1160, in Lyonshall, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Ranulph Marbury, was 24 and his mother, Mrs Randolph De Marbury, was 23. He married Mrs William De Marbury about 1184, in Weobley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1160–":"1160–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1165–Female":"1165–Surnud","1186–Male":"1186–Surnud","1136–1216":"1136–1216","1138–Female":"1138–Surnud","about 1184":"umbes 1184","1216":"1216","1138":"1138","1136":"1136","1165":"1165","1186":"1186","1160":"1160","Lyonshall, Herefordshire, England":"Lyonshall, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Weobley Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Weobley, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1160–":"1160–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1165–Female":"1165–Kuollut","1186–Male":"1186–Kuollut","1136–1216":"1136–1216","1138–Female":"1138–Kuollut","about 1184":"noin 1184","1216":"1216","1138":"1138","1136":"1136","1165":"1165","1186":"1186","1160":"1160","Lyonshall, Herefordshire, England":"Lyonshall, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Weobley Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Weobley, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1160–":"1160–Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","1165–Female":"1165–Décédée","1186–Male":"1186–Décédé","1136–1216":"1136–1216","1138–Female"